* Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above.JOHANNEBSURG Leaders of civil society, the religious community and political parties will brief the media about the formation of a people s movement.Opposition political parties have recently taken to streets to protest against President Jacob Zuma.They have called for his resignation or removal from office after his recent cabinet reshuffle which saw the axing of Pravin Gordhan and Mcebisi Jonas.Rating agencies Fitch and Standard and Poor have both since downgraded South Africa s economy to junk status.Two weeks ago the official opposition, the Democratic Alliance led a march against Zuma in Johannesburg while on the same day civil society organisation Save SA marched to the Union Buildings.Last week several opposition parties, led by their leaders, united in a march to the seat of government against the president.eNCA